Apple appears to have implemented a server-side fix for <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/09/26/iphone-17-apple-intelligence-bug/">an issue</a> that prevented a limited number of iPhone 17, iPhone Air, iPhone 17 Pro, and iPhone 17 Pro Max users from downloading on-device Apple Intelligence models.<br/>
<br/>
<img src="https://images.macrumors.com/article-new/2024/09/Apple-Intelligence-General-Feature-2.jpg" alt="" width="2500" height="1406" class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-963424" /><br/>
<em>MacRumors</em> contributor <a href="https://x.com/aaronp613/status/1975560120244576463">Aaron Perris</a> and <a href="https://x.com/tutti_creeper/status/1975555912162288048?s=46">others</a> who are impacted by this issue are now able to download the models and use Apple Intelligence features.<br/>
<br/>
The server-side fix applies automatically. On the iPhone 15 Pro and newer, you can check if Apple Intelligence is enabled in Settings → Apple Intelligence.<br/>
<br/>
Apple never publicly commented on the issue, so the underlying cause is unknown.<br/>
